how do i play with my chinchilla without losing his trust do you want to get your chin out of the cage if so and they are not wanting to be picked up as most chins are bait them with a dust bath take the dust house place it at the door of the cage when they jump in walk to the bathroom or other chin safe room and set the container down then you can sit there and enjoy watching and playing with them to get them back into the cage just wait until they go inside the dust bath and repeat the process eventually they will realize that you standing at the door of the cage is a good thing and you wont need the dust bath if your concerns are during playtime just sit quietly while they play they will run jump and leapfrog off the walls after a few weeks they will start to leapfrog off you and even sit on your shoulder a great forum for info about chins is http www chins n quills com forums The Inside Professional wrestling aerial techniques Professional wrestling throws Hamster The Fairly OddParents RuneScape quests The Shining (film) Aerial (dance move) The Curse of Fenric Sento Columbine High School massacre Professional wrestling attacks Salad Fingers Dog agility Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Swingout Professional wrestling holds Blonde on Blonde Boxing Shawn Michaels Silent Night, Deadly Night Domestic rabbit Toilet Blood Simple Syphon Filter Professional wrestling match types The Time Machine Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe John Cage Japanese tea ceremony Trapping Saw II Horse The Haunted Mansion Piccolo Junior Saga Treehouse of Horror V Tag The Visitation The Amber Spyglass G-Man (Half-Life) Dog training Dutch Schultz RuneScape locations Minor characters in Morrowind Muslim ibn Aqeel Baroque chess Equine conformation Volleyball Bathing 1957 World Series Conspiracy (TNG episode) Scream (film) Magic (illusion) Steel Cage Match Escape from New York Mario Eddie Guerrero GunZ The Duel Customs and etiquette of Japan Socrate Fancy rat Le